  levelNumber: 15
  levelName: Palenque
  location: Chiapas, Mexico
  levelDescription: "Where jungle meets stone, Palenque whispers the legacy of Pakal
    the Great.\n\nPalenque, known to the Maya as Lakamha (\u201CBig Water\u201D),
    was a powerful city-state in the lush foothills of Chiapas, Mexico. Founded around
    226 BC and flourishing between 600\u2013750 AD, it became one of the most influential
    Maya capitals of the Classic Period.\n\nThe city is best known for the Temple
    of the Inscriptions, which houses the tomb of K\u2019inich Janaab\u2019 Pakal
    (Pakal the Great), one of the most celebrated Maya rulers. Palenque\u2019s architecture
    is distinguished by its graceful palaces, temples, and carved panels, many of
    which record dynastic history and religious ceremonies."
